Key Things to Approach Greedy Problems
- Look for “Local Best Choice” - Greedy algorithms make the locally optimal choice at each iteration with the hope of finding a global optimum.
    Examples:
    Pick smallest weight
    Pick largest profit
- A problem has greedy property if making a local optimal choice leads to global optimal solution.
- Most greedy problems start with - Sort the input because greedy decisions usually depend on order.

Common Patterns in Greedy -
- Interval problems
- Cost minimization
- Profit maximization